ConverterManager controls the date and time converters.
 * <p>
 * This class enables additional conversion classes to be added via
 * {@link #addInstantConverter(InstantConverter)}, which may replace an
 * existing converter. Similar methods exist for misc.duration, time misc.period and
 * misc.interval converters.
 * <p>
 * This class is threadsafe, so adding/removing converters can be done at any
 * time. Updating the set of converters is relatively expensive, and so should
 * not be performed often.
 * <p>
 * The default misc.instant converters are:
 * <ul>
 * <li>ReadableInstant
 * <li>String
 * <li>Calendar
 * <li>Date (includes sql package subclasses)
 * <li>Long (milliseconds)
 * <li>null (now)
 * </ul>
 *
 * The default misc.partial converters are:
 * <ul>
 * <li>ReadablePartial
 * <li>ReadableInstant
 * <li>String
 * <li>Calendar
 * <li>Date (includes sql package subclasses)
 * <li>Long (milliseconds)
 * <li>null (now)
 * </ul>
 *
 * The default misc.duration converters are:
 * <ul>
 * <li>ReadableDuration
 * <li>ReadableInterval
 * <li>String
 * <li>Long (milliseconds)
 * <li>null (zero ms)
 * </ul>
 *
 * The default time misc.period converters are:
 * <ul>
 * <li>ReadablePeriod
 * <li>ReadableInterval
 * <li>String
 * <li>null (zero)
 * </ul>
 *
 * The default misc.interval converters are:
 * <ul>
 * <li>ReadableInterval
 * <li>String
 * <li>null (zero-length from now to now)
 * </ul>